import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('cx')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the cx field?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cy'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['cy'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['cy'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['cy'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['cy'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('cy')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the cy field?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_5_names = data['name'].value_counts().nlargest(5)
    plt.bar(top_5_names.index, top_5_names.values, color='blue')
    plt.title('What are the top 5 names in the name field?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    ax.boxplot(data['cx'], vert=False, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='red'))
    ax.set_title('What is the range of values in the cx field?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('cx')
    ax.set_ylabel('')

    return plt

chart = plot(data)
